This was tested using REST client by Huachao Mao

Using the following Scripts


--------------------------------------------------------

Productos

### 1. GET ALL PRODUCTOS
GET http://localhost:8080/api/productos

###

### 2. CREATE A NEW PRODUCTO (POST)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/productos
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "nombre": "Monitor LG",
    "descripcion": "70 pulgadas, PLASMA, 144hz",
    "precio": 200.21,
    "stock":20
}

###
###
POST http://localhost:8080/api/productos
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "nombre": "Monitor LG",
    "descripcion": "55 pulgadas, LED , 144hz",
    "precio": 150.21,
    "stock":20
}
###
### 3. UPDATE AN EXISTING PRODUCTO (PUT)
# Replace the '1' at the end with the actual ID from your H2 database
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/productos/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "nombre": "Monitor LG UltraWide",
    "descripcion": "Actualizado: 34 pulgadas, curvo"
    image
}

###

### 4. DELETE A PRODUCTO (DELETE)
# Replace the '1' with the ID you want to destroy
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/productos/1




---------------------------------------

Usuarios

### GET ALL USUARIOS
GET http://localhost:8080/api/usuarios

### CREATE USUARIO
POST http://localhost:8080/api/usuarios
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "nombreUsuario": "Juan Perez",
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "contrasenia": "sdahsfhasuf5#"
}

### UPDATE USUARIO
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/usuarios/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "nombre": "Edward Von Richtoffen",
    "email": "test2@example.com",
    "DNI": 12345678,
    "numeroTelefonico": "9988776655",
    "contrasenia": "dfhjsidhfgis3.2"
}
###
### Entrar a la pagina
POST http://localhost:8080/api/usuarios/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "sdahsfhasuf5#"
}
###
### DELETE USUARIO
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/usuarios/1
###

### Configuration
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/carritos
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Get all carts
# Calls carritoService.findAll()
GET {{baseUrl}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 2. Get a specific cart by ID
# Calls carritoService.findById(id)
GET {{baseUrl}}/1
Accept: {{contentType}}

###

### 3. Create a new cart (Initial setup)
# Calls carritoService.create(carrito)
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "nombreUsuario": "Juan Perez",
    "precioTotal": 0.0,
    "productos": []
}

###

### 4. Add a product to a cart
# Path: /api/carritos/{carritoId}/productos/{productoId}
# Calls carritoService.addProductoToCarrito, which recalculates the total price.
POST {{baseUrl}}/1/productos/3

###

### 5. Remove a product from a cart
# Path: /api/carritos/{carritoId}/productos/{productoId}
# Calls carritoService.removeProductoFromCarrito and updates total price.
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/1/productos/2

###

### 6. Delete the entire cart
# Calls carritoService.delete(id)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/1


